setup()
    Call drawly.start()
    Set a window title
    Set speed to 10 to make life less painful
    Use default window sizes (do nothing special)

reset() - Erase all of the patterns and start over
    draw a white rectangle to fill the screen

draw_rectangle_pattern()           *fix "rotation", currently not used*
    1. parameters
        center position - x, y of circular pattern
        offset - distance from center to top left corner of rectangle at 0 theta
        width - width of rectangle at 0 theta
        height - height of rectangle at 0 theta
        count - number of rectangles to draw
        rotation - number of degrees to rotate rectangle at 0 theta
            a. incrimentaly rotate each following rectangle by (360 / count)
    2. create loop count number of times with loop value equal to 360 / count (must allow floats & start at 0)
        Note: since range() does not allow fractional stepsize, create list of floats incrimentting each by 360/count
        a. call get_distance_point() to find x,y relative to 0, 0
            i. set distance argument to offset + height
            ii. set angle argument to loop value
            iii. return x_from_0, y_from_0
        c. call set_random_color()
        d. call rectangle()
            i. x is x_from_0 + center_x
            ii. y is y_from_0 + center_y
            iii. rotation is equal to loop value * -1 + rotation input * -1(make sure to round)
            iv. rotate from top left corner of rectangle at 0 theta(instead of center)



draw_circle_pattern()
    See additional information below
    1. parameters
        center position - x, y of circular pattern
        offset - distance from center to nearest point of any circle
        radius - radius of each circle
        count - number of circles to draw
    2. create loop count number of times with loop value equal to 360 / count (must allow floats & start at 0)
        Note: since range() does not allow fractional stepsize, create list of floats incrimentting each by 360/count
        a. call get_distance_point() to find x,y relative to 0, 0
            i. set distance argument to offset + radius
            ii. set angle argument to loop value
            iii. return x_from_0, y_from_0
        c. call set_random_color()
        d. call draw_circle() with x, y, radius
            i. x is x_from_0 + center_x
            ii. y is y_from_0 + center_y


draw_super_pattern()
    Parameter is the number of patterns to draw
    Use default of 5
    Randomly draw Rectangle and Circle patterns. Each pattern should be based on random values.
    Use reasonable random values (some can be negative) so patterns are drawn on the screen

set_random_color()
    1. create list of strings for possible colors
    3. set color to randomly chosen color

get_distance_point(distance, angle)
    1. parameters
        distance - distance from center of circle
        angle - angle in degrees
    2. calculate x and y coordinates of point on circle relative to 0, 0
    3. return x and y coordinates